    producer: "The New York City Opera Company (Julius Rudel, General Director)",
    performances: 3,
    synopsis: "The cast of the New York City Opera Company’s revival of Gian-Carlo Menotti’s The Medium included Claramae Turner, who had originated the role of Madame Flora in the opera’s world premiere at Columbia University’s Brander Matthews Theatre on May 8, 1946. For more information about the opera, see entries for the 1950 Broadway revival and City Opera’s 1959 revival (which also starred Turner).\n\nFor the current production, the opera was paired with another Menotti work, the one-act The Old Maid and the Thief, which was first heard on April 22, 1939, as a radio performance on NBC. The cast of the current revival of The Old Maid included Ruth Kobart and John Reardon.\n\nThe Medium and The Old Maid and the Thief were part of the opera company’s special spring season, which presented five weeks of ten contemporary American operas for a total of twenty-seven performances, including the world premiere of Robert Kurka’s The Good Soldier Schweik. The season was underwritten by a $105,000 grant from the Ford Foundation.",
