    tonyNominations: 5,
    wonBestMusical: false,
    performances: 711,
    funFact: "The concept album sold millions before the show ever reached the stage. It was one of the first musicals to be commercially successful as a recording before a single performance was staged.",
    synopsis: "Even though conceived as a theatre work, Jesus Christ Superstar appeared as a record before being presented on the stage because composer Andrew Lloyd Webber and lyricist Tim Rice were unable to find a producer willing to take a chance on so daring a production. Once it became a Gold Record album, however, the path was smoothed for its Broadway premiere. The self-described “rock opera” retold the last seven days of Christ in such a flamboyant, campy, and mind-blowing fashion that despite a mixed press and the opposition from various religious groups the show became a media hype and a boxoffice hit. The movie version was released in 1973 with Ted Neeley and Carl Anderson.",
