    synopsis: "Since Whistle premiered on Broadway, it has undergone little revision and has had only a few small-scale revivals. Merrily We Roll Along (Alvin; Nov. 16, '81; 16), on the other hand, is the show that refuses to die, undergoing constant revision and restaging in the decade since its New York opening. Its creation began when Harold Prince's wife suggested to her husband that he consider doing a show about teenagers. Prince thought of a forgotten 1934 play by George S.",
