    synopsis: "Updating the 1942 movie, Woman of the Year told a battle-of-the-sexes story with Lauren Bacall as Tess Harding, a Barbara Walters-type television personality, and Harry Guardino as Sam Craig, a satirical cartoonish suggesting Gary Trudeau. Angered by some television comments made by Tess about “funnies,” Sam retaliates by putting her in his strip as a character named “Tessie Cat.” The two meet, explode, marry, continue to explode, and eventually decide to try to work things out. Woman of the Year had certain points of similarity with Miss Bacall’s previous musical, Applause. Both shows were told in flashback, and both involved a strong-willed public personality trying to solve the problem of juggling a career and marriage. During the musical’s run, Miss Bacall was succeeded by Raquel Welch, Debbie Reynolds, and Louise Troy.",
