    synopsis: "Through explosive tap dancing and percussive storytelling, this musical chronicles the African-American experience from the arrival of slaves in 1619 through the Harlem Renaissance, the civil rights era, and into modern urban life. Savion Glover's furious, rhythmic footwork becomes the heartbeat of Black history, telling stories of joy, oppression, and resilience that words alone cannot express.",
